North Horr MP Chachu Ganya and his Saku counterpart Ali Rasso have been arrested in connection with the deadly Marsabit clashes that have claimed 14 lives. The two leaders were arrested on Monday and taken for questioning at DCI headquarters. Last week they were grilled by DCI officers in Embu over their involvement in the skirmishes. Governor Ali Mohamud Mohamed was also questioned. After they were grilled, the leaders accused security teams of failing to play their role to prevent conflicts in Marsabit. Read: Governor Ali, two MPs quizzed over Marsabit ethnic clashes Hundreds of people have fled their homes since the sporadic clashes erupted in September with more officers being deployed there. Read: Four killed as Borana, Gabra clash in Marsabit Click here for the latest political news